Translation:
Marduk and Zarpanitu, your gods, whose feet you have grasped, will make the king, my lord, successful in whatever the king, my lord, does. (        
mim-ma ma-la LUGAL be-lí-a ip-pu-šú šu-nu-ma ina ŠU.2 LUGAL be-lí-ia ú-šal-la-am)
Notes: šullumu X ina qāti Y = to make X thrive in the hands of Y; slightly literary?

Translation: grasped the feet of the king, my lord, (ina GÌR.2 LUGAL be-lí-ia aṣ-ṣa-bat)
Notes: Unclear why there is 'ina' here unless it's a mistake

Translation: do not grasp the feet of the king, (at-ta i-na GÌR.2-MEŠ šá LUGAL la ta-ṣab-bat )
